<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="405" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6212/26</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Administrator of the National Recovery
                                    Administration</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-23">January 23, 1934</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Replying to yours of
                                January 12th, I have no suggestions to make about the circular of
                                the League for the Defense of Jewish Rights because regardless of
                                what they may say about the Swastika we are anxious to have people
                                patronize the Blue Eagle.</p>
                            <p>Sincerely,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hugh S.
                                Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>